		"Holy canceled bar tab!  You think he's related to Jonathan?" Scrap said as he scratched his eyebrow with a pencil. <br/><br/>"Ya think?" I said as I rolled my eyes.  "Janelle?  Is Jeffry related to Jonathan Allison?" <br/><br/>Janelle wandered over from her desk and looked at the employee record on my screen.  "Oh yes.  That is Mr. Allison's brother.  He's been here forever." <br/><br/>Scrap quietly chuckled until I fed him an elbow into the ribs.<br/><br/>"Dude, this is pretty messed up right here.  So let's see - you have Jeffry, Tomas, Jose and the unidentified driver all in on this?" Scrap said as he rubbed his bruised rib.  <br/><br/>"Yep.  I think we need to go old school on this." I said as I jotted down the names of all TA truck drivers.  "And we're going to need a little professional help." <br/><br/>Scrap and I excused ourselves outside of the TA building.  While Scrap lit a cigarette, I scrolled through phone numbers on my Treo looking for an old, reliable friend named Jon Voyte.  Jon was a [[private investigator]] that specialized in [[surveillance]] and had helped me out on several previous cases including <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100707132216/http://blogs.ittoolbox.com/security/investigator/archives/000258.asp">The Case Of The Heartless Husband</a>.<br/><br/>I selected Jon's number on my Treo and listened to it ring a number of times. <br/><br/>"Jon speaking." <br/><br/>I cleared my throat.  "Jon, it's Chief.  Is there anyway you could meet me at Allison Technologies tomorrow evening?  I know it's short notice."<br/><br/>Jon paused for a moment as he checked his schedule.  <br/><br/>"I think I could do that.  What's the gig, and how much?" Jon asked.  I could hear the smile on his face.<br/><br/>"Standard fee.  We have a real cartoon show here to monitor." I said as I described the events of the case.<br/><br/>"What a nightmare." Jon said.  "I can deploy all the [[wireless cameras]] you want, and we can place the digital recorder in a vehicle outside.  You know me, I can rig anything." <br/><br/>I laughed.  "You don't have to brag to me.  I like the idea of placing the recorder in a vehicle, I'm not sure how safe it would be in the building.  You may have to babysit."<br/><br/>"I'm cool with that.  Now let's talk strategy." Jon suggested.  <br/><br/>An hour later the plan was formed, and Scrap &amp; I decided to prepare for a bit of impromptu surveillance in the morning.<br/><br/>"Do I need to pick up coffee and doughnuts in the morning?" Scrap  said with a <br/>hearty laugh.  "This is straight out of a bad police show." <br/><br/>"I have you covered.  Just bring your camera, and make sure you get some sleep tonight.  No late night IRC chatting with babes!" I demanded while waving my cell phone around.<br/><br/>Tomorrow morning was garage sale time.<p><hr><table width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFCC" cellpadding="9px">
